added.title: Open Door Policy
added.description: Still shipwrecked on a desert island, the Titans try to find food but stumble upon dinosaurs instead.

added.title: Operation Tin Man
added.description: Gizmo convinces the Titans he's kidnapped Cyborg, when in reality Cyborg's just hanging out in the HIVE tower with his girl Jinx. When Gizmo gets annoyed by Cyborg's constant presence, the two start a prank war.

added.title: Laundry Day
added.description: When the gang bickers over whose turn it is to do chores, things quickly get out of control until their dirty uniforms grow a mind of their own and attack!

added.title: La Larva de Amor
added.description: The gang agrees to babysit Silkie but then loses him. Meanwhile, Silkie has a telenovela adventure south of the border.

added.title: Girls' Night Out
added.description: When the guys plan a guys night out, Starfire drags Raven out on a wild adventure of their own.

added.title: The Boredom
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are convinced it's one of those days when nothing interesting is happening. But as they walk around Elmore in search of adventure, it becomes apparent exciting things are happening just not to them.

added.title: The Code
added.description: Gumball learns the Wattersons have been stealing Mr. Robinson's wi-fi for years. When it goes down, they try and live without it but life offline proves too hard. Gumball and Darwin decide to hack their way through cyberspace to learn Mr Robinson's passcode.

added.title: The Console
added.description: When Gumball is given a cursed videogame console, Elmore becomes trapped inside a fantasy RPG world. Gumball, Darwin and Anais have to battle their way through town, unraveling the secrets of their new virtual reality. But they'll have to level up if they're going to stand any chance against the mysterious final boss.

added.title: The Catfish
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin realise Grandpa Louie has no friends on Elmore Plus, they feel bad so they create one called Muriel. However when Granny Jojo finds out Louie has been spending time online with another 'woman', Muriel not existing isn't going to stop her from being destroyed.

added.title: The Diet
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover the reason Dad's diet wasn't working was that he was actually on ten diets and eating a meal for each of them. They eventually manage to help him lose weight, but Richard's newfound buffness also brings out his more obnoxious side.

added.title: Boss For a Day
added.description: When Chata lets Vic be the boss of the taco stand for the day Vic decides to fire Val, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: Aluxes
added.description: When Vic finds an ancient relic that summons a gang of mischievous creatures, he uses them to do his bidding, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: Guillermo's Gathering
added.description: When Vic & Val are forced to go to Guillermo's boring birthday party, they devise a scheme to leave early, but end up discovering that the party is way cooler than they thought.

added.title: Balloon Boys
added.description: Vic & Val go on a hot air balloon trip with Sal and compete to be his favorite, but things go awry when they try to use the magical Nazca Lines to their advantage.

added.title: Barn Mates
added.description: Steven helps two friends get along at the barn.

added.title: Beach City Drift
added.description: Steven and Connie get into a high-speed car race with their biggest foe.

added.title: Chille Tid
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems try to relax with a slumber party.

added.title: Cry for Help
added.description: Steven's favorite TV show gets interrupted by a magical disturbance.

added.title: Catch and Release
added.description: We finally see inside Steven's bathroom.

added.title: Inglorious Toddlers
added.description: Owen fears he's about to lose his BFF Noah to a gifted military school.

added.title: All the Little People
added.description: Magic Man secretly slips Finn a bag filled with miniature versions of Finn and all his friends.

added.title: Davey
added.description: Finn can't go anywhere without folks stopping to thank him for being a hero.

added.title: Dungeon Train
added.description: Finn and Jake discover a train where every car is a dungeon filled with a new foe for Finn to fight. Jake gets bored and wants to leave, but Finn is having the best time and doesn't want to leave ever!

added.title: Apple Wedding
added.description: You are cordially invited to the wedding of the year! But who will be united in matrimony?

added.title: Bad Timing
added.description: Love is in the air when Lumpy Space Princess reconnects with an old classmate, but will her jealousy get in the way of finding true love?

added.title: Dawn of the Donut
added.description: Dr. Fox's plans to deliver donuts all over the Unikingdom are sidetracked by Unikitty's reluctance to follow instructions.

added.title: The New Nemesis
added.description: When Hawkodile discovers his old enemy Eagleator has a new nemesis in his life, the gang do all they can to get Hawk back on his foe's radar.

added.title: Baby Caterpillar
added.description: Unikitty takes in a radioactive caterpillar and raises it like a baby, unaware of the havoc it will wreak as a full-grown adult.

added.title: Borrowed
added.description: Richard discovers his library books have been borrowed by Master Frown and sets off on a crazed mission to return the books before they're overdue.

added.title: Best Best Friends
added.description: Master Frown and Brock attend a friendship-themed competition intending to ruin it for everyone else, but soon discover their own friendship in need of repair.

added.title: The Escape Room of Doom
added.description: The gang infiltrate an escape room game center to thwart Score Creeper, but their former foe claims he only works there to pay the bills.

added.title: Stop, Drop and Side Scroll
added.description: Our ninja barely have time to mourn the loss of their fallen ninja friends before being thrust into the madness of Terra Domina where Lloyd will have to face an old adversary from his past.

added.title: Ninjago Confidential
added.description: Back in Ninjago City, Zane and Pixal hit the mean streets to track down Milton Dyer, only to discover that things are not what they seem.

added.title: The Prodigal Father
added.description: Zane, kidnapped by the Mechanic, faces Unagami. Master Wu fights to free Zane, while Pixal questions Milton Dyer for information on how to shut down Prime Empire.

added.title: The Temple of Madness
added.description: Jay must stand alone against Unagami in the end-game, yet Unagami has a bigger battle in facing the truth about his own identity.

added.title: Game Over
added.description: Unagami breaks into the real world and terrorizes Ninjago City while Jay, Zane and Pixal attempt to prevent disaster by reuniting Unagami with his creator, Milton Dyer.

added.title: Planet X
added.description: When Rad returns to his home planet, he learns a shocking truth about alien society.

added.title: Let's Meet Sonic
added.description: When world class hero SONIC THE HEDGEHOG visits the plaza, he teams up with KO to save the day.

added.title: Radical Rescue
added.description: Rad is forced to reconsider his identity when KO starts taking on some of his traits.

added.title: Red Action 3: Grudgement Day
added.description: KO and Enid attempt to prevent a mysterious power battle between Rad and Red Action.

added.title: Thank You for Watching the Show
added.description: When KO finds moments of his life slipping by, he begins to suspect something weird is going on.

added.title: Inventor Mentor
added.description: Uncle Grandpa goes to Italy to help a young girl who wants to be a great inventor.

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 2
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: Public Radio
added.description: After listening to a public radio broadcast during class, Clarence is inspired to record a radio interview of his own featuring his buddy Sumo. When Ms. Baker hears the charming interview, she calls in a favor and gets Clarence a spot on the actual Aberdale Public Radio! The search is on - to find the perfect interview subject for his big day.

added.title: Dinosaur Day
added.description: Pizza Steve's jealousy ruins Uncle Grandpa's Dinosaur Day celebration for Mr. Gus.

added.title: Gilben's Different
added.description: Gilben's newly sprouted peach fuzz sparks a discussion about puberty that ultimately convinces Clarence to act more like an adult.

added.title: Uncle Melvins
added.description: Legendary rock band, the Melvins, team up with Uncle Grandpa to help a young girl who wants to win her school's talent show.

added.title: Cool Guy Clarence
added.description: When Clarence meets JT, the kid who mows their lawn, he finds a fast friend who shows him some cool new music, a new outlook on life and a sweet rat-tail! Clarence leans into the rat tail lifestyle, discovering a whole new side of Aberdale he never knew existed.

added.title: Don't Drink the Water
added.description: In Florida, Ben and Max accidentally come in contact with water from The Fountain of Youth. As a result, Max transforms into a kid and Ben a toddler, with Gwen having to deal with both of them. Our trio then must track down Hex who's found the source of the fountain and prevent him from drinking the water that will make him immortal and unstoppable.

added.title: Costume Crisis
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes improvements to a kid's Halloween costume.

added.title: Bald Spot
added.description: Muscle Man wants to hide his bald spot at all costs.

added.title: Missing Cat
added.description: When Chelsea accidentally lets her pet cat Crumbles out, the cat goes missing! Reluctant to ask for help, she struggles to find the cat before anyone realizes it's gone. It's up to cat whisperer Clarence to interject and find Crumbles, whether Chelsea wants his help or not!

added.title: Chill Out
added.description: Uncle Grandpa takes a kid to the North Pole for an epic snowball battle.

added.title: A Bunch of Full Grown Geese
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to get rid of some geese that are causing problems at the park.

added.title: Video Store
added.description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo visit their local video store to rent a movie, but discover it's all rented out! Each of them have a different idea of what tape to bring home, and must enlist the help of a tie breaker to figure it out.

added.title: Carter and Briggs
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby enter a donut contest to win a cameo on their favorite cop show.

added.title: Blind Trust
added.description: Benson has to trust Mordecai and Rigby to get him down a mountain.

added.title: Largo
added.description: When a mysterious rain cloud plagues Townsville, Bubbles learns things aren't what they seem.

added.title: In the Doghouse
added.description: Buttercup must go it alone to save her family from a kidnapping.

added.title: Hustlecup
added.description: When Buttercup loses the Professor's latest invention, she'll have to beat The Gangreen Gang at their own game to get it back.

added.title: Drama Bomb
added.description: The school play goes off the rails when the drama teacher interferes.

added.title: Amor de hermanos
added.description: Después de romper la planta de Chata, Vic y Val deben cumplir con la tarea aparentemente fácil de reemplazarla, lo cual demuestra no serlo cuando sus disputas ponen en peligro Monte Macabro.

added.title: Hunted
added.description: Three alien bounty hunters are hot on Ben's trail. But one of them is a secret agent trying to make sure the Omnitrix does not fall into evil hands.

added.title: Jefe por un dia
added.description: Cuando Chata deja que Vic sea el jefe del puesto de tacos por un día, él decide despedir a Val, lo que trae consecuencias desastrosas.

added.title: Rules of Engagement
added.description: Princess Looma returns to claim Ben as her husband, and she's not going to let anyone stand in her way!  (Featuring Julie and Ship.)

added.title: Halt and Catch Silico
added.description: When a series of negative articles about the Powerpuff Girls are posted on the Internet, the girls track them back to Silico.

added.title: Return to Forever
added.description: The Forever Knights threaten to use a sinister weapon to erase all alien DNA on Earth unless Ben and Rook can stop them.

added.title: OTTO Motive
added.description: Kevin and Rook run into an old enemy from the Null Void while attending an intergalactic auto show. (Re-introducing classic Ben alien, Upgrade.)

added.title: Max's Monster
added.description: Grandpa Max's old Plumber partner, Phil, seeks Max's help to tame the monster within. (Introducing new Ben alien, Buzzshock; Re-introducing old Ben alien, Benvicktor.)

added.title: Mystery, Incorporeal
added.description: An old enemy emerges while Ben and Rook visit Kevin and Gwen at college.

added.title: Ninos de Globo
added.description: Vic y Val salen de viaje en globo aerostático con Sal y compiten por ser su favorito, pero las cosas se complican cuando tratan de usar las mágicas líneas de Nazca a su favor.

added.title: La Fiesta de Guillermo
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val se ven forzados a ir a la aburrida fiesta de cumpleaños de Guillermo, crean un plan para irse temprano, pero terminan descubriendo que la fiesta es mucho mejor de lo que pensaban.

added.title: Aluxes
added.description: Vic encuentra una antigua reliquia que invoca a una pandilla de traviesas criaturas, iy las consecuencias son desastrosas!

added.title: Taladro
added.description: Pantro se está hartando de tener que arreglar cosas constantemente por todo el Cubil Felino, lo cual es una pena porque los Thundercats están a punto de ser atacados por un robot perforador imparable...ique va a romper todo!

added.title: Exodo Parte 1
added.description: En el estreno de dos partes de la serie, León-O y los Thundercats escapan de la destrucción del mundo en el que viven, Thundera, y terminan estrellándose en el misterioso, peligroso y absolutamente increíble Tercer Planeta. Pero sus enemigos, los Mutantes de Plun-Darr, los siguieron. Y resulta que el Tercer Planeta ya tiene un problema llamado Mumm-Ra. ¿Puede León-O aprender las reglas para ser un líder a tiempo?

added.title: La Broma
added.description: Cuando intenta demostrarles a los Thundercachorros que no es un adulto aburrido (como Tigro), León-O ignora sus instintos y se mete con un cristal claramente malvado.

added.title: La Espada Perdida
added.description: A León-O le recuerdan que debe conectar la Espada del Augurio al Cubil Felino todas las noches o la base se quedará sin energía. No hay problema, no es que León-O vaya a perder accidentalmente la espada o algo así, ¿verdad?

added.title: Pantro robado
added.description: Buitro tiene un nuevo invento, pero hay un gran problema: ile robó la idea a Pantro! Ah, y además Buitro usa su invento para apoderarse del Tercer Planeta. De modo que hay dos grandes problemas.

added.title: Exodo Parte 2
added.description: En el estreno de dos partes de la serie, León-O y los Thundercats escapan de la destrucción del mundo en el que viven, Thundera, y terminan estrellándose en el misterioso, peligroso y absolutamente increíble Tercer Planeta. Pero sus enemigos, los Mutantes de Plun-Darr, los siguieron. Y resulta que el Tercer Planeta ya tiene un problema llamado Mumm-Ra. ¿Puede León-O aprender las reglas para ser un líder a tiempo?

added.title: La invasion de las guerreras amazonas
added.description: El Tercer Planeta está siendo invadido por Guerreras Amazonas con fuerza y músculos extraordinarios iy parece que los Thundercats son los siguientes en su lista de ataques! Ahora, la seguridad de todos dependerá de los Thundercachorros, aunque sean tan pequeños y las Guerreras Amazonas sean tan grandes.

added.title: La Leyenda de Boggy Ben
added.description: León-O se apoderó del último frasco de Thundersnaps, ilas mejores galletas disponibles en Thundera! Pero un frasco de galletas difícil de abrir hace que León-O y Chitara terminen yendo tras la leyenda de Boggy Ben.

added.title: El secreto del unicornio
added.description: Un unicornio que llora aparece en el Cubil Felino y, entre lágrimas, les dice a los Thundercats que todos sus amigos unicornios han sido capturados. Tigro se cree un experto en el tema que podrá ayudar al último de los unicornios...Solo necesita que deje de llorar lo suficiente para decirle quién se llevó a sus amigos. Es más fácil decirlo que hacerlo, viejo.

added.title: El terror en la Montana Hook
added.description: Tigro lleva a León-O a la cima de la Montaña Hook para enseñarle una lección sobre la confianza. Pero cuando quedan atrapados por una tormenta de nieve y se refugian en una espeluznante cabaña propiedad del espeluznante Snowman, lo que se pondrá a prueba es la capacidad de Tigro para confiar.
